The samples were dried in a SpeedVac and resuspended in 50 mM ammonium bicarbonate prior to LC-MS analysis.
pr_nif_0000_03266_2.extract: Human serum samples were denatured and reduced with 60% methanol and 10 mM dithiothreitol (DTT) at 60Â°C for 1 h and alkylated with 50 mM iodoacetamide (IAM) at room temperature in the dark for 30 min.
